<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
3. 
<taxonomicName LSID="3ACD7A58-3FBB-530A-83AD-2748A0651891" authority="Diels, Notes Roy. Bot. Gard. Edinburgh 5: 284. (1912) ≡ Camellia forrestii (Diels) Cohen-Stuart" authorityName="Diels, Notes Roy. Bot. Gard. Edinburgh 5: 284. (1912) ≡ Camellia forrestii (Diels) Cohen-Stuart" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Theaceae" genus="Thea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Thea forrestii" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="forrestii">Thea forrestii Diels, Notes Roy. Bot. Gard. Edinburgh 5: 284. (1912) ≡ Camellia forrestii (Diels) Cohen-Stuart</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="lectotype">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Lectotype.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
(designated here; first-step designated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sealy, JR" journalOrPublisher="The Royal Horticultural Society, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" refId="B15" refString="Sealy, JR, 1958. A Revision of the Genus Camellia. The Royal Horticultural Society, London" title="A Revision of the Genus Camellia." year="1958">Sealy 1958</bibRefCitation>
: 54): China. Yunnan: South end of Tsu-hsiong-fu (Chuxiong) Valley, 7000-8000 ft alt., February 1903, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">G. Forrest 314</emphasis>
(E00284407!; its image is available at http://data.rbge.org.uk/herb/E00284407).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
<bibRefCitation author="Diels, L" journalOrPublisher="Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" pagination="161 - 304" refId="B7" refString="Diels, L, 1912. Plantae Chinenses Forrestianae: New and imperfectly known species. Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh 5: 161 - 304" title="Plantae Chinenses Forrestianae: New and imperfectly known species." volume="5" year="1912">Diels (1912)</bibRefCitation>
cited a single gathering, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">G. Forrest 314</emphasis>
, as the type of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Theaceae" genus="T." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="T. forrestii" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="forrestii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">T. forrestii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the protologue. 
<bibRefCitation author="Cohen-Stuart, CP" journalOrPublisher="Mededeelingen van het Proefstation voor Thee" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" pagination="1 - 328" refId="B6" refString="Cohen-Stuart, CP, 1916. Voorbereidende onderzoekingen ten dienste van de selektie der theeplant. Mededeelingen van het Proefstation voor Thee 40: 1 - 328" title="Voorbereidende onderzoekingen ten dienste van de selektie der theeplant." volume="40" year="1916">Cohen-Stuart (1916)</bibRefCitation>
transferred this species into 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Theaceae" genus="Camellia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Camellia" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Camellia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without any comment on the type. However, three duplicates of 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">G. Forrest 314</emphasis>
were found at E (E00284407), K (K000380522) and P (P04511547), so they are syntypes of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Theaceae" genus="T." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="T. forrestii" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="forrestii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">T. forrestii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Art. 40 Note 1 of the ICN). When 
<bibRefCitation author="Sealy, JR" journalOrPublisher="The Royal Horticultural Society, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" refId="B15" refString="Sealy, JR, 1958. A Revision of the Genus Camellia. The Royal Horticultural Society, London" title="A Revision of the Genus Camellia." year="1958">Sealy (1958</bibRefCitation>
: 54) indicated &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Forrest 314</emphasis>
(E, K; type of 
<taxonomicName genus="C." lsidName="C. forrestii" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" rank="species" species="forrestii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">C. forrestii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
)&quot;, such citation may act as the first-step lectotypification under Art 9.17 of the ICN. It is further narrowed to a single specimen at E (E00284407) here as the second-step lectotype of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Theaceae" genus="T." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="T. forrestii" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="forrestii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">T. forrestii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
